values:
I have pictures for this post, but since I used David's fancy-pants camera I can't upload them yet.

I finished getting the plants in today, 4 cucumbers, 3 jalapenos, 3 habanero, and 2 strawberries.&nbsp; 
When I was putting the strawberries in I thought, "I should throw in those dead strawberry roots I bought earlier this month, let them fertilize the healthy ones."&nbsp;&nbsp; See, I had planted the root bundles in old seedling containers, and they never grew any&nbsp; plants so I thought they were dead.&nbsp; When I dumped them out, I found 2 with growing roots and 5 with little plants than never made it through the soil.&nbsp;&nbsp; I've got them in larger pots now, with little plants poking out.&nbsp; If they all come through I may need to get another strawberry pot!

The cucumbers finish out the line of vegetable, behind tomatoes and next to eggplants.&nbsp; The peppers have their container, as they are technically David's.&nbsp; I was through with peppers after the surprising yield last year that we are still working through.&nbsp; Yet when I asked him if he wanted me to plant anything for him he said he wanted his own container of jalapenos and habaneros.&nbsp; Perhaps keeping them next to the strawberries will keep the birds away.&nbsp; 

I also threw in some garlic, 4 cloves from the fridge that already had a little over an inch of green growing.&nbsp; Garlic is suppose to be planted in the fall, just before the first frost so it can incubate underground for a couple of months.&nbsp; I don't really expect to get any bulbs from this, but like many vegetables, there is more than one edible part of the plant.&nbsp; The flower and green parts of garlic are suppose have a very delicate flavor, and if the potatoes are any indicator, this store bought garlic will at least yield green parts.

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

Two things I found interesting:

On the way to lunch I over heard two women complaining about transsexuals.&nbsp;&nbsp;Not because&nbsp;of their lifestyle choice, but&nbsp;because they thought the way some&nbsp;transsexuals&nbsp;dressed showed an unrealistic image&nbsp;of femininity.&nbsp; "All that teased up&nbsp;Dolly Parton hair"&nbsp;

When conducting a research study involving young children, it is considered more favorable to compensate the child with something that will give them direct enjoyment (like a gift certificate to a toy store) than with money, since that will probably end&nbsp;up&nbsp;at the parents discretion.
